  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Greetings from Peter'
      title: Greetings from Peter
      number: 1
      content: '  This letter is from Simon[[COMMENT(0)]] Peter, a slave and apostle
        of Jesus Christ.I am writing to you who share the same precious faith we
        have. This faith was given to you because of the justice and fairness[[COMMENT(1)]]
        of Jesus Christ, our God and Savior.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:1a '
        content: Greek <b>Simeon.</b>
      - number: '1:1b '
        content: Or <b>to you in the righteousness.</b>
    - name: '2: Growing in Faith'
      title: Growing in Faith
      number: 2
      content: 'May God give you more and more grace and peace as you grow in your
        knowledge of God and Jesus our Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'By his divine power, God has given us everything we need for living
        a godly life. We have received all of this by coming to know him, the one
        who called us to himself by means of his marvelous glory and excellence. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And because of his glory and excellence, he has given us great and
        precious promises. These are the promises that enable you to share his divine
        nature and escape the world\u2019s corruption caused by human desires.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "In view of all this, make every effort to respond to God\u2019s promises.
        Supplement your faith with a generous provision of moral excellence, and
        moral excellence with knowledge, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'and knowledge with self-control, and self-control with patient endurance,
        and patient endurance with godliness, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'and godliness with brotherly affection, and brotherly affection with
        love for everyone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The more you grow like this, the more productive and useful you will
        be in your knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But those who fail to develop in this way are shortsighted or blind,
        forgetting that they have been cleansed from their old sins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] work hard to prove that
        you really are among those God has called and chosen. Do these things, and
        you will never fall away. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:10 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - name: '11: Paying Attention to Scripture'
      title: Paying Attention to Scripture
      number: 11
      content: 'Then God will give you a grand entrance into the eternal Kingdom
        of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore, I will always remind you about these things\u2014even
        though you already know them and are standing firm in the truth you have
        been taught. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And it is only right that I should keep on reminding you as long
        as I live.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:13 '
        content: Greek <b>as long as I am in this tent </b>[or <b>tabernacle</b>].
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For our Lord Jesus Christ has shown me that I must soon leave this
        earthly life,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: Greek <b>I must soon put off my tent </b>[or <b>tabernacle</b>].
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'so I will work hard to make sure you always remember these things
        after I am gone.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For we were not making up clever stories when we told you about the
        powerful coming of our Lord Jesus Christ. We saw his majestic splendor with
        our own eyes '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "when he received honor and glory from God the Father. The voice from
        the majestic glory of God said to him, \u201CThis is my dearly loved Son,
        who brings me great joy.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:17 '
        content: Matt 17:5; Mark 9:7; Luke 9:35.
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'We ourselves heard that voice from heaven when we were with him on
        the holy mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Because of that experience, we have even greater confidence in the
        message proclaimed by the prophets. You must pay close attention to what
        they wrote, for their words are like a lamp shining in a dark place\u2014until
        the Day dawns, and Christ the Morning Star shines[[COMMENT(0)]] in your hearts. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        content: Or <b>rises.</b>
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Above all, you must realize that no prophecy in Scripture ever came
        from the prophet\u2019s own understanding,[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:20 '
        content: "Or <b>is a matter of one\u2019s own interpretation.</b>"
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: or from human initiative. No, those prophets were moved by the Holy
        Spirit, and they spoke from God.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Danger of False Teachers'
      title: The Danger of False Teachers
      number: 1
      content: '  But there were also false prophets in Israel, just as there will
        be false teachers among you. They will cleverly teach destructive heresies
        and even deny the Master who bought them. In this way, they will bring sudden
        destruction on themselves. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Many will follow their evil teaching and shameful immorality. And
        because of these teachers, the way of truth will be slandered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In their greed they will make up clever lies to get hold of your
        money. But God condemned them long ago, and their destruction will not be
        delayed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For God did not spare even the angels who sinned. He threw them into
        hell,[[COMMENT(0)]] in gloomy pits of darkness,[[COMMENT(1)]] where they
        are being held until the day of judgment. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:4a '
        content: Greek <b>Tartarus.</b>
      - number: '2:4b '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>in chains of gloom.</b>
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And God did not spare the ancient world\u2014except for Noah and
        the seven others in his family. Noah warned the world of God\u2019s righteous
        judgment. So God protected Noah when he destroyed the world of ungodly people
        with a vast flood. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Later, God condemned the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah and turned
        them into heaps of ashes. He made them an example of what will happen to
        ungodly people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But God also rescued Lot out of Sodom because he was a righteous
        man who was sick of the shameful immorality of the wicked people around him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Yes, Lot was a righteous man who was tormented in his soul by the
        wickedness he saw and heard day after day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So you see, the Lord knows how to rescue godly people from their
        trials, even while keeping the wicked under punishment until the day of final
        judgment. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He is especially hard on those who follow their own twisted sexual
        desire, and who despise authority.These people are proud and arrogant, daring
        even to scoff at supernatural beings[[COMMENT(0)]] without so much as trembling. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:10 '
        content: Greek <b>at glorious ones, </b>which are probably evil angels.
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the angels, who are far greater in power and strength, do not
        dare to bring from the Lord[[COMMENT(0)]] a charge of blasphemy against those
        supernatural beings.  '
      comments:
      - number: '2:11 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>to the Lord; </b>still others do not include
          this phrase at all.
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'These false teachers are like unthinking animals, creatures of instinct,
        born to be caught and destroyed. They scoff at things they do not understand,
        and like animals, they will be destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Their destruction is their reward for the harm they have done. They
        love to indulge in evil pleasures in broad daylight. They are a disgrace
        and a stain among you. They delight in deception[[COMMENT(0)]] even as they
        eat with you in your fellowship meals. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:13 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>in fellowship meals.</b>
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "They commit adultery with their eyes, and their desire for sin is
        never satisfied. They lure unstable people into sin, and they are well trained
        in greed. They live under God\u2019s curse. "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They have wandered off the right road and followed the footsteps
        of Balaam son of Beor,[[COMMENT(0)]] who loved to earn money by doing wrong. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:15 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>Bosor.</b>
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But Balaam was stopped from his mad course when his donkey rebuked
        him with a human voice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'These people are as useless as dried-up springs or as mist blown
        away by the wind. They are doomed to blackest darkness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They brag about themselves with empty, foolish boasting. With an
        appeal to twisted sexual desires, they lure back into sin those who have
        barely escaped from a lifestyle of deception. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They promise freedom, but they themselves are slaves of sin and corruption.
        For you are a slave to whatever controls you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when people escape from the wickedness of the world by knowing
        our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ and then get tangled up and enslaved by
        sin again, they are worse off than before. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'It would be better if they had never known the way to righteousness
        than to know it and then reject the command they were given to live a holy
        life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "They prove the truth of this proverb: \u201CA dog returns to its
        vomit.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]] And another says, \u201CA washed pig returns to
        the mud.\u201D"
      comments:
      - number: '2:22 '
        content: Prov 26:11.
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Day of the Lord Is Coming'
      title: The Day of the Lord Is Coming
      number: 1
      content: '  This is my second letter to you, dear friends, and in both of them
        I have tried to stimulate your wholesome thinking and refresh your memory. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I want you to remember what the holy prophets said long ago and what
        our Lord and Savior commanded through your apostles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Most importantly, I want to remind you that in the last days scoffers
        will come, mocking the truth and following their own desires. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "They will say, \u201CWhat happened to the promise that Jesus is coming
        again? From before the times of our ancestors, everything has remained the
        same since the world was first created.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They deliberately forget that God made the heavens long ago by the
        word of his command, and he brought the earth out from the water and surrounded
        it with water. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then he used the water to destroy the ancient world with a mighty
        flood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And by the same word, the present heavens and earth have been stored
        up for fire. They are being kept for the day of judgment, when ungodly people
        will be destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But you must not forget this one thing, dear friends: A day is like
        a thousand years to the Lord, and a thousand years is like a day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "The Lord isn\u2019t really being slow about his promise, as some
        people think. No, he is being patient for your sake. He does not want anyone
        to be destroyed, but wants everyone to repent. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But the day of the Lord will come as unexpectedly as a thief. Then
        the heavens will pass away with a terrible noise, and the very elements themselves
        will disappear in fire, and the earth and everything on it will be found
        to deserve judgment.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '3:10 '
        content: Other manuscripts read <b>will be burned up; </b>one early manuscript
          reads <b>will be found destroyed.</b>
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Since everything around us is going to be destroyed like this, what
        holy and godly lives you should live, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'looking forward to the day of God and hurrying it along. On that
        day, he will set the heavens on fire, and the elements will melt away in
        the flames. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But we are looking forward to the new heavens and new earth he has
        promised, a world filled with God\u2019s righteousness.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And so, dear friends, while you are waiting for these things to happen,
        make every effort to be found living peaceful lives that are pure and blameless
        in his sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And remember, our Lord\u2019s patience gives people time to be saved.
        This is what our beloved brother Paul also wrote to you with the wisdom God
        gave him\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: "16: Peter\u2019s Final Words"
      title: "Peter\u2019s Final Words"
      number: 16
      content: 'speaking of these things in all of his letters. Some of his comments
        are hard to understand, and those who are ignorant and unstable have twisted
        his letters to mean something quite different, just as they do with other
        parts of Scripture. And this will result in their destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'You already know these things, dear friends. So be on guard; then
        you will not be carried away by the errors of these wicked people and lose
        your own secure footing. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: Rather, you must grow in the grace and knowledge of our Lord and Savior
        Jesus Christ.All glory to him, both now and forever! Amen.
      comments: []
